%h1
  Debian

%p
  If you are running on a
  %a{:href => "http://www.debian.org/misc/children-distros"}
    Debian Based System
  Then the dependencies you should install are:

%p
  For JRuby (if you wish to use it) you will need:

%pre.code
  :preserve
    apt-get install curl sun-java6-bin sun-java6-jre sun-java6-jdk
%P
  Note that you have to add the partner repository has to be enabled
  as a software source because that's the new location of the Sun Java packages.
  %pre.code
    :preserve
      System -> Administration -> Software Sources -> Other Software
  (If anyone can tell me how this is done by editing files in the OS I'd appreciate it)

%p
  For MRI & ree (if you wish to use it) you will need:
%pre.code
  :preserve
    apt-get install curl bison build-essential zlib1g-dev libssl-dev libreadline5-dev libxml2-dev git-core

%p
  For IronRuby (if you wish to use it) you will need:
%pre.code
  :preserve
    apt-get install curl mono-2.0-devel

